<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>First, fix the link. I had to cut and paste it, removing the ][/link] off the end to get it to work. <br /> <br />Second, Give up on the &quot;tanking cleric&quot; idea, it won't work. Yes, in a pinch, you can gear up so you can take a hit or two, but you will NEVER be an effective tank.  <br /> <br />Focus primarily on getting your mana pool up, getting mana regen, and getting the important focus effects. <br /> <br />Obviously, the easiest upgrade to identify is your head slot. Magnetic is a nice upgrade. Same for the gauntlets. <br /> <br />Replace one of your earrings with a solstice earring. You need mana regen. I would replace the boots with ornate, as they have mana preservation 4 as an effect, however, since you already have MP3 in back slot, thats not a big priority. You could go with boots of slaughter, or magnetic for now. I would also get ornate for both wrist slots, for an additional mana regen 4. The runed mithril bracer should obviously be replaced first. Girdle of Mithaniel is a nice upgrade for your waist. If that's too pricy, even magnetic would be better. A ring of thunderous spirit would be a nice upgrade for the bloody ancille's ring, and the thunderous spirit rings are usually pretty cheap. <br /> <br />Just a few suggestions. Click on my name to check out my cleric's gear, to get an idea what you can gear a cleric up like without raiding.</p>
