<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>If you are going to tank you will need to get some haste.  Go to the Bazaar and see what is available, but be warned haste is not cheap!  Also use Elixir of Speed to quicken your attack.  Obviously you are going to use your Hammer of Judgment as your primary weapon, you are also going to need a shield in order to bash.   I recommend Stormguard armor, with symbol, for your armor up grade.  It is cheap and offers a good all round rise in your abilities. Your agility is way to low, look for an augmentation with plus +12 AGI in the Bazaar.  The spell Protection of Vie or Ward of Vie is often overlooked, but you will need it to mitigate the damage that is coming your way.  Yaulp V is your best friend.  Don’t let others discourage from melee combat.  If you want to tank more power to you just remember you will never be as skilled as a warrior.  Most important, you can not tank and perform your duties as a cleric.  A group needs a dedicated healer, if you try and do both you are going to get someone killed and perpetuate the myth that clerics can’t tank. </p>
