<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>I am a &quot;Battle Cleric&quot;, while this worked great up untill the high 50's, I still get into the mix when I have a tank that can stand up to the damage. Don't lvl to say 40, or 50, and say one day, I'm tired of sitting and healing, I think I'm gona be a battle cleric, you'll get your arse handed to you. You have to work your skills up as you level, bash, dodge, etc. You will NEVER have the damage mitigation of a tank, but it helps. I had to retire to the traditional roll of cleric (sit and heal) as I progressed to WOS and above, I am often stealing agro on perpose from the tank, in BOT and such just to mess around and agravate my tank (a friend).  I took my time leveling, by gettina 130 AA's before I hit lvl 67 so I could play tank in bot and lower planes lvl's. Tanking BOT was cake last time I was there (around lvl 65), but you have to be willing to set your toon up for it. Spend the time to get good gear, and to get the AA's to help you take damage, but you HAVE to remember, if you want to group, your first priority is to take care of your group. Get your mana, and healing abilities up. Don't expect to tank WOS or higher untill your lvl 70 with hundreds of AA's and Uber gear. I last as a lvl 68, 140 AA's, about 3 or 4 hits in MPG.  <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Sat Nov  5 07:58:46 2005 by aBarberian</span></i></p>
